
THE TEN COMMANDMENTS

0. YOU SHALL NOT HIDE TYPE NAMES BEHIND TYPEDEFS
1. YOU SHALL NOT NEST HEADER INCLUDES
2. YOU SHALL DECLARE PRIVATE FUNCTIONS AND VARIABLES AS STATIC
3. YOU SHALL FAVOR CONSTANTS OVER DEFINES
4. YOU SHALL USE TABS FOR INDENTATION
5. YOU SHALL USE THE ONE TRUE BRACE STYLE
6. YOU SHALL NOT CAST VOID POINTERS
7. YOU SHALL USE PROPER GRAMMAR AND PUNCTUATION IN COMMENTS
8. YOU SHALL LEARN TO USE C11 TO YOUR ADVANTAGE
9. YOU SHALL USE TASTE AND GOOD JUDGEMENT IN ALL YOUR ENDEAVORS
